<subSubSection id="C3605DCCFFF3FF93FF73F8DE41F01DC2" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="598" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC50E47FFF3FF92FF73F8DE406C1B43" blockId="2.[151,1436,1803,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">
<emphasis id="B90ED255FFF3FF92FF73F8DE45531B24" box="[197,309,1803,1826]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B90ED255FFF3FF92FF73F8DE45481B24" bold="true" box="[197,302,1803,1826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">Remarks</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The species was collected sieving soil with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A75C4FFF3FF92FCABF8DE400F1B24" authority="Miller" authorityName="Miller" box="[797,1129,1803,1826]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Lavandula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis id="B90ED255FFF3FF92FCABF8DE407D1B24" box="[797,1051,1803,1826]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">Lavandula angustifolia</emphasis>
Miller
</taxonomicName>
, at about 
<quantity id="4C82A3A2FFF3FF92FB62F8DE41791B24" box="[1236,1311,1803,1826]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500m</quantity>
altitude, in bush along the eastward path from the pass and leading to Madonna della Guardia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC50E47FFF3FF92FF73F885462D1BF4" blockId="2.[151,1436,1803,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">
Electron scanning microscopy (Quanta 200, FEI) revealed the presence of sensilla on the penis (
<figureCitation id="134112C2FFF3FF92FB76F885416A1B61" box="[1216,1292,1872,1895]" captionStart="PLATE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,238,1182,1205]" captionTargetBox="[179,1400,211,1152]" captionTargetId="figure-190@2.[166,1420,194,1158]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="PLATE 2. Meira diottii sp. n.: 4. Penis, lateral view; 5. Apex of the penis, dorsal view; 6. genital armature of the internal sac, typical of the genus; 7. Supplementary genital armature of the internal sac; 8a, 8b. sensilla of the penis (SEM)." pageId="2" pageNumber="597">Plate 2</figureCitation>
, figs. 8a, 8b), earlier observed in various species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A75C4FFF3FF92FD87F8A646C71B8C" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[561,673,1907,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carabidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A75C4FFF3FF92FD1AF8A647371B8C" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[684,849,1907,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chrysomelidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A75C4FFF3FF92FCEAF8A640601B8C" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[860,1030,1907,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Megalopodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megalopodidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A75C4FFF3FF92FBA7F8A640C11B8C" authorityName="C.G. Thomson" authorityYear="1859" box="[1041,1191,1907,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Orsodacnidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Orsodacnidae</taxonomicName>
, but, to the best of our knowledge, only recently documented for the first time in a weevil (
<taxonomicName id="4C7A75C4FFF3FF92FC34F84340711BAB" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1891" box="[898,1047,1942,1965]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Cleistolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90ED255FFF3FF92FC34F84340711BAB" box="[898,1047,1942,1965]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="597">Cleistolophus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sp. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A75C4FFF3FF92FBFAF84340DB1BAB" box="[1100,1213,1942,1965]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="597" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Entiminae">Entiminae</taxonomicName>
) by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB73B6FFF3FF92FB58F843455D1BC9" author="Dungelhoef, S. &amp; Schmitt, M." pageId="2" pageNumber="597" pagination="45 - 57" refId="ref1515" refString="Dungelhoef, S. &amp; Schmitt, M. (2010) Genital feelers: the putative role of parameres and aedeagal sensilla in Coleoptera Phytophaga (Insecta). Genetica, 138, 45 - 57. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10709 - 009 - 9404 - 9" type="journal article" year="2010">Düngelhoef and Schmitt (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. The authors suggest that the sensilla might provide the male with information on the position and shape of the female opening during copulation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC50E47FFF2FF93FF73FF4D453A1D11" blockId="3.[151,1436,152,452]" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">
<emphasis id="B90ED255FFF2FF93FF73FF4D45C51CA9" bold="true" box="[197,419,152,175]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="598" reason="1">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7A75C4FFF2FF93FE1FFF4D46571CA9" authorityName="Pierotti &amp; Fink" authorityYear="2013" box="[425,561,152,175]" class="Exobasidiomycetes" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Fungi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="598" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="diottii">
<emphasis id="B90ED255FFF2FF93FE1FFF4D46571CA9" box="[425,561,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">Meira diottii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A75C4FFF2FF93FD0AFF4D40E21CA9" authority="Sainte-Claire Deville, 1906" authorityName="Sainte-Claire Deville" authorityYear="1906" box="[700,1156,152,175]" class="Exobasidiomycetes" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Fungi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="598" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="stierlini">
<emphasis id="B90ED255FFF2FF93FD0AFF4D47311CA9" box="[700,855,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">Meira stierlini</emphasis>
Sainte-Claire Deville, 1906
</taxonomicName>
, by its short elytra, its less gibbous clypeus, its unicolored scales and highly elongate form, and from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A75C4FFF2FF93FC57FF6F416B1CD7" authority="Stierlin 1892" authorityName="Stierlin" authorityYear="1892" box="[993,1293,186,209]" class="Exobasidiomycetes" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Fungi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="598" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="baudii">
<emphasis id="B90ED255FFF2FF93FC57FF6F40151CD7" box="[993,1139,186,209]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">Meira baudii</emphasis>
Stierlin 1892
</taxonomicName>
(topotypical specimens from Rome) by its very robust antennae, and from every other 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A75C4FFF2FF93FC06FF0847971CF2" baseAuthorityName="Jacquelin du Val" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[944,1009,221,244]" class="Exobasidiomycetes" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Fungi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="598" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90ED255FFF2FF93FC06FF0847971CF2" box="[944,1009,221,244]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">Meira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the supplementary genital armature of the internal sac.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC50E47FFF2FF93FF73FEF746831D79" blockId="3.[151,1436,152,452]" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">
This new species shows affinities particularly with a set of specimens from 
<collectingRegion id="49BEC0A5FFF2FF93FBB2FEF740391D3F" box="[1028,1119,290,313]" country="Italy" name="Toscana" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">Tuscany</collectingRegion>
considered at this time to be belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A75C4FFF2FF93FE93FE90466C1D5A" authority="Stierlin" authorityName="Stierlin" authorityYear="1892" box="[293,522,325,348]" class="Exobasidiomycetes" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Fungi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="598" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="baudii">
<emphasis id="B90ED255FFF2FF93FE93FE9045D71D5A" box="[293,433,325,348]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">Meira baudii</emphasis>
Stierlin
</taxonomicName>
, and with the topotypic specimens of that species (around Rome) and those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A75C4FFF2FF93FAEDFE9045B41D79" authority="Sainte-Claire Deville" authorityName="Sainte-Claire Deville" authorityYear="1906" class="Exobasidiomycetes" family="Curculionidae" genus="Meira" kingdom="Fungi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="598" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="stierlini">
<emphasis id="B90ED255FFF2FF93FAEDFE90448C1D79" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">Meira stierlini</emphasis>
Sainte-Claire Deville
</taxonomicName>
(Nice region, La Turbie).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC50E47FFF2FF93FF73FE5F41F01DC2" blockId="3.[151,1436,152,452]" pageId="3" pageNumber="598">The specimens from the Ligurian coast exhibit elytral scales with lighter and irregular spotting, shorter and less raised setae, and supplementary armature of the internal sac of the penis rather different from the topotypical specimens.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
